import pandas as pd
from sqlalchemy import create_engine

# Database connection parameters
db_name = 'TrafficData'
db_user = 'postgres'
db_password = 'pavlov3'
db_host = 'localhost'
db_port = '5432'


# Create a connection string
connection_string = f'postgresql://{db_user}:{db_password}@{db_host}:{db_port}/{db_name}'

# Create a database engine
engine = create_engine(connection_string)

# Query to load data
query = "SELECT * FROM accidents2 LIMIT 7000000"

# Load data into a Pandas DataFrame
df = pd.read_sql(query, engine)

print(df.head())

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from matplotlib.ticker import FuncFormatter
sns.set(style="white")

# Create the bar plot with customizations
fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(5, 4))  # Adjust the figure size as needed
grouped_df.plot(kind='bar', stacked=False, ax=ax, color=sns.color_palette("viridis", len(grouped_df.columns)),width=.5)

# Customize the plot
plt.xlabel('Severity', fontsize=11)
plt.ylabel('Count', fontsize=11)
plt.title('Distribution of Severity by Sunrise/Sunset ', fontsize=12)
plt.xticks(rotation=0, fontsize=10)
plt.yticks(fontsize=10)

# Add a legend with a title
plt.legend(title='Sunrise/Sunset', title_fontsize='11', fontsize='10')

# Format the y-axis to display as actual numbers
ax.yaxis.set_major_formatter(FuncFormatter(lambda x, _: f'{int(x):}'))

ax.grid(False)
# Show the plot
plt.tight_layout()  # Adjust the layout to make room for the labels and title
plt.show()

numerical_columns = ['severity', 'distance_mi','temperature_f','wind_chill_f','wind_speed_mph','precipitation_in', 'start_time_month']

mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(correlation_matrix, dtype=bool))

In [18]:
df_numerical = df.copy()
non_numerical_columns = [
    'id', 'source', 'start_time', 'end_time', 'description', 'street', 'city', 'county', 'state', 
    'zipcode', 'country', 'timezone', 'airport_code', 'weather_timestamp', 
    'wind_direction', 'weather_condition', 'sunrise_sunset', 'civil_twilight', 
    'nautical_twilight', 'astronomical_twilight'
]
boolean_columns = df_numerical.select_dtypes(include=['bool']).columns
df_numerical[boolean_columns] = df_numerical[boolean_columns].astype(int)

df_numerical = df_numerical.drop(columns=non_numerical_columns)
numerical_columns = df_numerical.select_dtypes(include=['number']).columns
df_numerical = df_numerical[numerical_columns]
correlation_matrix1 = df_numerical.corr()
# Generate a mask for the upper triangle
mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(correlation_matrix1, dtype=bool))

# Set up the matplotlib figure with a larger size
plt.figure(figsize=(18, 12))

# Draw the heatmap with customizations
sns.heatmap(
    correlation_matrix1, 
    mask=mask, 
    annot=True, 
    cmap='coolwarm', 
    linewidths=0.5, 
    cbar_kws={"shrink": .8, "label": "Correlation Coefficient"},  # Custom color bar
    square=True,  # Ensures the heatmap cells are square
    annot_kws={"size": 11, "weight": "bold"},  # Annotation font size and weight
    fmt=".2f"  # Format for the annotation text
)

# Customize the title and labels
plt.title('Correlation Matrix Heatmap', fontsize=20, fontweight='bold')
plt.xticks(fontsize=12, rotation=45, ha='right')
plt.yticks(fontsize=12, rotation=0)

# Adjust layout to make room for labels
plt.tight_layout()

# Show the plot
plt.show()
